@startuml Comment_System_Sequence_Detailed
!theme blueprint
title Comment System - Real-time Comments & Interactions

actor User as U
participant "PostDetail UI\n(Vue Component)" as FE
participant "Posts Store\n(Pinia State)" as PS
participant "API Client\n(HTTP Service)" as API
participant "Backend API\n(api.localtest.me:3001)" as BE
database "PostgreSQL\nDatabase" as DB

== Phase 1: Load Comments for Post ==
U -> FE: 1. Open PostDetail modal
note right: User clicks on post to view details

FE -> PS: 2. loadComments(postId)
PS -> PS: 3. Set loadingComments = true
note right
**Loading State Management:**
```typescript
const loadingComments = ref(false);
const postComments = ref<Comment[]>([]);
```
**UI Indicators:**
- Show loading spinner
- Disable comment form
- Display skeleton comments
end note

PS -> API: 4. fetchComments(postId)
API -> BE: 5. GET /api/comments/:postId
note right
**API Request Details:**
- URL: /api/comments/{postId}
- Method: GET
- Headers: Authorization Bearer token
- Purpose: Fetch all comments for post
end note

== Phase 2: Database Comment Retrieval ==
BE -> BE: 6. Validate session & extract user
note right
**Authentication Process:**
```typescript
const user = await authenticateUser(request);
```
**Security Validation:**
- Bearer token verification
- Session validity check
- User permission validation
end note

BE -> DB: 7. SELECT comments with author info & like status
note right
**Complex JOIN Query:**
```sql
SELECT 
  c.id, c.content, c.created_at, c.likes_count,
  u.id as author_id, u.name, u.email, u.picture,
  EXISTS(
    SELECT 1 FROM comment_likes cl 
    WHERE cl.comment_id = c.id 
    AND cl.user_id = $user_id
  ) as is_liked
FROM comments c
JOIN users u ON c.author_id = u.id
WHERE c.post_id = $post_id
ORDER BY c.created_at DESC;
```
**Features:**
- Author information included
- Personal like status
- Optimized single query
end note

DB --> BE: 8. Comments with author data & like status
BE --> API: 9. JSON response with comments array
note right
**Response Format:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "comment-uuid",
      "content": "Great post!",
      "author": {
        "id": "user-uuid",
        "name": "John Doe",
        "picture": "avatar-url"
      },
      "likes_count": 5,
      "is_liked": true,
      "created_at": "2025-08-04T10:30:00Z"
    }
  ],
  "message": "Retrieved 10 comments"
}
```
end note

API --> PS: 10. Comments array
PS -> PS: 11. Set postComments = comments
PS -> PS: 12. Set loadingComments = false
PS --> FE: 13. Comments ready for display
FE -> U: 14. Display formatted comments list

== Phase 3: Create New Comment ==
U -> FE: 15. Type comment and click "Post Comment"
note right: User writes comment in text area

FE -> FE: 16. Validate comment content
note right
**Frontend Validation:**
```typescript
const validateComment = (content: string) => {
  if (!content.trim()) {
    throw new Error('Comment cannot be empty');
  }
  if (content.length > 1000) {
    throw new Error('Comment too long');
  }
  return content.trim();
};
```
**Validation Rules:**
- Non-empty content required
- Maximum length limit
- XSS prevention (sanitization)
end note

FE -> PS: 17. submitComment(content, postId)
PS -> API: 18. createComment({postId, content})
API -> BE: 19. POST /api/comments
note right
**API Request Details:**
- URL: /api/comments
- Method: POST
- Headers: Authorization Bearer + Content-Type
- Body: {"postId": "uuid", "content": "text"}
end note

== Phase 4: Comment Database Creation ==
BE -> BE: 20. Validate session & content
note right
**Backend Validation:**
```typescript
const validation = {
  user: await authenticateUser(request),
  postId: validateUUID(body.postId),
  content: sanitizeContent(body.content)
};
```
**Security Measures:**
- User authentication required
- UUID format validation
- Content sanitization
- Rate limiting (future)
end note

BE -> DB: 21. INSERT INTO comments
note right
**Comment Creation Query:**
```sql
INSERT INTO comments (
  id, post_id, author_id, content, created_at
) VALUES (
  uuid_generate_v4(), $1, $2, $3, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
) RETURNING *;
```
**Database Triggers:**
- Auto-increment posts.comments_count
- Update post.updated_at timestamp
end note

DB -> DB: 22. Trigger updates posts.comments_count
BE -> DB: 23. SELECT new comment with author info
note right
**Fetch Complete Comment:**
```sql
SELECT 
  c.*, u.name, u.email, u.picture,
  false as is_liked, 0 as likes_count
FROM comments c
JOIN users u ON c.author_id = u.id
WHERE c.id = $comment_id;
```
end note

DB --> BE: 24. Complete comment object with author
BE --> API: 25. New comment response
note right
**Success Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": "new-comment-uuid",
    "content": "User's comment text",
    "author": {
      "id": "user-uuid",
